Load Training DataSet¶

In [24]:
def get_image (mode):
    labels = []
    images = []
    level = 0
    base_path = os.getcwd()
    mode_path = os.path.join(base_path, mode)
    
    if mode == 'seg_pred':
        for img in os.listdir(mode_path):

            img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(mode_path, img))
            resize_image = cv2.resize(img,(128, 128))
            images.append(resize_image)
            labels.append(level)
        
        return shuffle(images, labels, random_state=100)

    for label in os.listdir(mode_path):
        if label == 'buildings':
            level = 0
        elif label == 'forest':
            level = 1
        elif label == 'glacier':
            level = 2
        elif label == 'mountain':
            level = 3
        elif label == 'sea':
            level = 4
        elif label == 'street':
            level = 5
        
        for img in os.listdir(os.path.join(mode_path, label))
            img = cv2.imread(os.path.join(mode_path, label, img))
            resize_image = cv2.resize(img,(128, 128))
            images.append(resize_image)
            labels.append(level)

    return shuffle(images, labels, random_state=100)

images = np.array(images)
labels = np.array(labels)
In [6]:
def get_class_name(code):
    labels = { 0:'buildings', 1:'forest', 2:'glacier', 3:'mountain', 4:'sea', 5:'street'}
    return labels[code]

        # BGR images
        ax[i,j].imshow(images[random_number])
        ax[i,j].set_title(get_class_name(labels[random_number]))
        ax[i,j].axis('off')

Model¶

In [8]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(200,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',input_shape=(128,128,3)))
model.add(Conv2D(180,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(5,5))
model.add(Conv2D(180,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv2D(140,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv2D(100,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv2D(50,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(5,5))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(180,activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(100,activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(50,activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(rate=0.5))
model.add(Dense(6,activation='softmax'))
model.summary()

model.compile(optimizer=Adam(lr=0.0001), loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])

# Validation data : 30 % from training datset
history = model.fit(images, labels ,epochs=35, validation_split=0.30)
